<subSubSection pageId="106" pageNumber="107" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="106.[151,1437,1868,2039]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,218,1868,1894]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Notes</emphasis>
. The both 
<typeStatus box="[351,465,1868,1894]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">lectotypes</typeStatus>
were studied about 30 years ago and the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blackburn" authorityYear="1902" box="[1124,1350,1868,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Brachypeplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olliffi">
<emphasis box="[1124,1350,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Brachypeplus olliffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lea" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Brachypeplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">B. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was established. Few years later 
<specimenCount box="[620,760,1904,1931]" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
, quite distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blackburn" authorityYear="1902" box="[990,1213,1904,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Brachypeplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olliffi">
<emphasis box="[990,1213,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Brachypeplus olliffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lea" authorityYear="1925" box="[1254,1373,1905,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Brachypeplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis" status="syn. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1254,1373,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">B. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="106" pageNumber="107">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
) were found and for them a new species is here proposed. In order to check the formerly established synonymy the authors asked 
<collectingRegion box="[358,403,1977,2003]" country="Switzerland" name="Bern" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">Ben</collectingRegion>
Parslow (SAM) and Dmitry Telnov (NHML) to compare pictures of species with the type specimens. The redescription of this species was done on base of the type specimens of 
<emphasis box="[1135,1261,2013,2038]" italics="true" pageId="106" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lea" authorityYear="1925" box="[1135,1257,2013,2038]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Brachypeplus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="106" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">B. insignis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
